WEBVTT

00:08:59.511 --> 00:09:00.677
examining this.

00:09:00.701 --> 00:09:03.219
Let me walk you through
an example of one patient.

00:09:04.766 --> 00:09:07.593
Here's an example of one patient
who undergoes surgery

00:09:07.617 --> 00:09:08.785
at time point zero,

00:09:08.809 --> 00:09:11.291
and then undergoes chemotherapy.

00:09:11.709 --> 00:09:14.194
Then the patient is under remission.

00:09:14.218 --> 00:09:18.827
He is monitored using clinical exams
and imaging methods.

00:09:19.149 --> 00:09:24.052
Around day 450, unfortunately,
the cancer comes back.

00:09:25.266 --> 00:09:27.751
The question is:
Are we able to catch this earlier?

00:09:27.775 --> 00:09:31.520
During this whole time,
we've been collecting blood serially